<subSubSection id="F94BAE41F7B773BFCC0C9A42CCDEEA17" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B44FD556DEEB538594AA524E3684FC1E" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">
<taxonomicName id="EC6E76892F1D6F81ADD1DC8FB15E4AEF" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stereocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Stereocerus</taxonomicName>
Kirby, 1837: 34. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="26FA5B0A46432E596A16F3362AE3E1AC" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stereocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="42944B4098AC740F172D740E8293629B" italics="true" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">Stereocerus similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kirby, 1837 (= 
<taxonomicName id="82B6936594D212855292DAF8AEE8FB2C" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematopus">
<emphasis id="E31E379A93861DF598F45148D1302E87" italics="true" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">Feronia haematopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831) by monotypy. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="E38340D66653FB669E5ECAF256CEC512" italics="true" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">stereos</emphasis>
(solid, firm, hard) and 
<emphasis id="802C9F73FEFDF8D516E9122198AABC13" italics="true" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">ceros</emphasis>
(horn, by extension antenna), alluding to the stout antennae (&quot;antennae robust&quot;) of the adults [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1EB31B7492168F19C04B72E7B6D520AD" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">
<taxonomicName id="670EAB98606D9590D81F8DB49CBF3705" authorityName="Tschitscherine" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Boreobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Boreobia</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="50B67A0C2C236D6E3A82A6796B28AA7A" originalValue="Tschitschérine">Tschitscherine</normalizedToken>
, 1896b: 375. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="942AEE43CA510FAA3DCD86FF9E1FD27E" authorityName="Tschitscherine" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imitatrix">
<emphasis id="8AFD2847385E1CBD254C20A1C7CA6172" italics="true" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">Feronia imitatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="8F23E3ED65B01EB9FD8FD2E39583636D" originalValue="Tschitschérine">Tschitscherine</normalizedToken>
, 1896 (= 
<taxonomicName id="5DD4B3B0A592174F862026B3057F0B34" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematopus">
<emphasis id="A2237E786544C63BF12078F601678BA2" italics="true" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">Feronia haematopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831) designated by Bousquet (1984a: 4). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="2C6AB63C1E12BAC6C36A0DBBD5902138" italics="true" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">boreas</emphasis>
(north) and 
<emphasis id="37E40CD30A2AF4C2C992525FFC26E01B" italics="true" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">bios</emphasis>
(life) [feminine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="37B3093AA58E94C99EBBFA657531838D" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="00285679DCA44C90EB71216C2B0E74ED" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="43979DA8A6E8439FD0CB2299C1F64A12" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">Two Holarctic species in the arctic, subarctic, and boreal regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C680DA182B59614F024BE8ADF7DB854" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" type="identification">
<paragraph id="EB87111B384B1E28B50D77B26DF9FB22" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="52E2A60340068156B236BA89B5FA1A9C" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">
Lindroth (1966) redescribed both species and provided a mean for their identification through his key to Canadian species of 
<taxonomicName id="865457D38C1CC9392F2115B32CA0A205" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="501" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="97ED980CE614FB2D6A73EA398A3CD3DE" italics="true" pageId="501" pageNumber="502">Pterostichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
